$ %CommonProgramFiles(x86)%

The default location for `%CommonProgramFiles(x86)%` seems to be `C:\Program Files (x86)\Common Files`.

 
sa:
  `CommonFilesDir (x86)` under the → Windows/registry[registry] key
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion`]

  `CommonFilesDir` under → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Wow6432Node/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\WOW643Node\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion`]

  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Common-Files[`%CommonProgramFiles%`]

  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86[`%ProgramFiles(x86)%`]

  The → Microsoft/dot-net enumeration → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Environment/SpecialFolder[`System.Environment+SpecialFolder`].
